Quintessential neighborhood bar with the absolute BEST fried mushrooms, fries, and nachos anywhere in the city. Killer draft list and patio that thankfully will never show up on any best-of-Chicago lists.  My first spot when bars reopen.

This is mine and my fiance's favorite little hang out. They always have a great beer selection on draft, it's hard to pick just one, so count on have at least 2 or 3. The wings and cheese curds are excellent, but my favorite thing on the menu is the quesadilla. They are so damn good and they come with this magical sour cream (it's got a hint of lime, so good). We've got my fiance's father hooked, whenever he comes to visit he wants Small Bar quesadillas.

Love any place that offers waffle fries, tater tots AND sweet potato fries as options. Great place to watch a game, chill with friends on a rainy day, or go on the patio when it’s nice out! Another great neighborhood joint. Yes, Logan Square is a very trendy neighborhood. But, there are still vestiges of the up and coming neighborhood. The place is on a corner, it is literally a small place, with a great selection of craft tap beer, good selection of liquor.  The service is good, the vibe is friendly, and I hope it never gets gentrified like the Gold Star Bar.

Small Bar gave me the best bar experience I have had in years. After our soccer match, a large group went for food and drinks and they were helpful with moving tables, giving great suggestions on food, and prompt forward-thinking service. The pulled pork is a must try and the buffalo wings were great. More bars need to take Small Bar's lead on how to provide a great experience, our team decided after one visit that it is our official after match spot.

Great rotating draft selection and proper food menu. Tater tots are extraterrestrial tasty and the bartenders recognize you immediately. Parking is usually o.k. unless it snows. If you like dive bars but don't want to shower after this is the place to go.

Every morning around 2:20 am, I am graced with the outlandish and sleep disrupting noise of the owner or employee's vroom vroom toy. It's so exciting going to bed at night knowing I have to wake up early, but what makes it more exciting is the fact that I get to be absolutely terrified coming from a dead sleep almost 3 hours before I have to wake up. Maybe his friends or mom said it was a cool thing to have the loudest toy on the block but I can't imagine why. The drunk people who stagger out of there have never even been an issue. But hey, at least everyone knows where you are at all times buddy. Gave 2 stars cause the food is good every so often.

Sit out on the patio with your dog in nice weather!  I was surprised to find that the food at Small Bar was top-notch. It's a great pub dinner in a relaxing atmosphere. The bartenders are more than amenable to changing the TV to whatever obscure sporting event you're trying to watch.  Favorite menu items: 1) Fried Cheese Curds - served with mustard, this plate has enough for two to snakc on while watching a game or waiting on an entree  2) Buffalo Chicken Sandwich - An enormous chicken breast fired and smothered in buffalo sauce, served with fries and not-quite-enough blue cheese (just ask for more!) I usually eat half and bring the other half home for lunch the next day.
Large beer selection and a laid-back neighborhood atmosphere make this worth visiting even though it's a little off the beaten path. Outdoor patio currently open as well.

When I go to small bar I get a bunch of well bourbon and cokes.  I also enjoy getting sliders and pretending that they are full sized burgers.  Making me a giant if you look at the size difference of burger to hand.  Feeling like a bridge troll is the only way I can truly unwind after a long day of not drinking trash.  Love this place.
R.I.P. this was my favorite bar and now it's gone. Personally I thought their burgers were even better than Kuma's across the street. The place that replaced it is not as good.

Looks like your average run-of-the-mill cozy neighborhood dive, but it was so much more!   An incredible beer list (they had Burbon County on tap!), and the food (I had the fried cheese curds appetizer and a burger with waffle fries) was easily the best I have ever had! I am going to make this a regular stop, and you should too.

Great food, amazing beer selection, friendly staff that genuinely seems happy to be at work.  A wonderful and quiet outside patio that is one of my favorite places in Chicago.  Possibly my favorite bar, at least in the top 3.

Small Bar has a big taste. The vitalizing eats menu offers great-tasting bar food standards, but also incorporates a menu of ever-changing selections of delicious specials, including a unique and filling bowl of macaroni and cheese that is always tossed with a slew of new ingredients that (seemingly) change every day. Drop by often for the drink menu too, it's always changing with daily drink specials. They've even offered exclusive brews not typically available to the public. In the Summer the patio opens up offering a little bit more room to spread out for lunch, a late afternoon drink or two, a date, or dinner with friends. Things can get louder and fairly crowded on the weekends but generally speaking, it's a homey environment with a diverse demographic of people, and the staff absolutely rocks.

Truly great beer list. Always friendly service and I really like the vibe of this place. I had sliders (with cheese, $1.50 each on Tuesdays). I wouldn't get them again. A soft, tiny pretzel bun and an even smaller patty, with a few slices of pickles on the side. The patties were extremely well (over)done. I also got to try the veggie burger, and waffle fries with beer cheese, which was all good. Perhaps the food is hit or miss, but the beer and environment is reason enough to return.
Great beer selection, friendly staff, really delicious wings.
Total neighborhood bar. However, the staff was super friendly & drinks weren't hard to come by. I didn't feel like an outsider.
Great neighborhood gem. The food is great and the staff is awesome!

This is a good bar. Previously I had a 4 star rating, but after going here twice changed it to 5 stars because you can bring your parrot inside. Their appetizers are good and the staff is very friendly. I would stick up for them in a prison shower fight

Went for the beer on tap, website keeps it updated as well as beer finder. Great little bar, very friendly people. Pulled pork was great but a tad spicy for BBQ and burgers had a delicious char taste to them. Kudos for a proper medium temperature which no one seems to get right anymore. Only thing is I felt that the beer wasn't quite served cold enough. Other than that, I'll come back again at some point. Oh cheese curds! Yum.

It's been a little while since my last visit, but the patio of this hidden outpost of Small Bar is the best in terms of laid-back vibes, great brews, and standard bar food. Staff are extremely knowledgable about what's on tap, what pairs with what, etc.. Meanwhile, the fried foods are, well, densely crisp and exactly what you'd need on a warm day with a cold, crisp IPA. Definitely prefer this Small Bar over its other locations.
